  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "With the enhancement of container restart backoff, pod phase may not progress monotonically.\n\nA pod is considered running if at least one container in the pod has been started. If the container happens to be crashlooping, the restart backoff would eventually kick in. From that point on, the container status becomes waiting, and [kubelet determines the phase](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go#L2497) as **pending**.\n\nOnce the pod transitions from `Running` to `Pending`, it's impossible to retrieve logs from the crashlooping container using kubectl. This prevents the users from debugging the cause of container failures.\n\n``` console\n$ kubectl logs -p heapster-v10-3ayyj --namespace=kube-system\nError from server: Internal error occurred: Pod \"heapster-v10-3ayyj\" in namespace \"kube-system\" : pod is not in 'Running', 'Succeeded' or 'Failed' state - State: \"Pending\"\n```\n\nAn easy fix is to check `LastTerminationState` of a container before determining the pod phase.\n\n/cc @samsabed \n",
